The paper deals with a synchronous message passing system with processors that are subject to crash failures, which falls under the category of distributed computing (cs.DC). The focus on work complexity and communication complexity suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-categories of data structures (cs.DS) and information theory (cs.IT). The use of algorithms to solve the Do-All problem suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-category of distributed algorithms (cs.Distributed). Finally, the mention of effort as a measure of overall efficiency suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-category of systems and control (cs.SY).
